# Markdown Syntax
@divider

Marque supports standard Markdown syntax for content formatting, plus a set of extended syntax elements for tables, code highlighting, task lists, and more. Use the summary panel to jump to any element.

@callout .info
###* Basic vs. Extended
Basic syntax is supported by nearly all Markdown processors. Extended syntax requires processor support — Marque supports all elements listed on this page.
@end callout

# Basic Syntax
@divider

@card .primary
## Headings
@divider

| syntax | output |
| --- | --- |
| `# H1` through `###### H6` | `<h1>` through `<h6>` |
| `===` underline | heading level 1 |
| `---` underline | heading level 2 |

@demo "Hash syntax"
#* Heading 1
##* Heading 2
###* Heading 3
####* Heading 4
#####* Heading 5
######* Heading 6
@end demo

@demo "Alternate underline syntax"
Heading level 1
===============*

Heading level 2
---------------*
@end demo

@callout .warn
Always put a space between `#` and the heading text. Put blank lines before and after headings for compatibility.
@end callout
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Paragraphs
@divider

| syntax | output |
| --- | --- |
| blank line between text | new `<p>` paragraph |
| two trailing spaces + return | `<br>` line break |

@demo "Paragraphs"
This is the first paragraph.

This is the second paragraph.
@end demo

@demo "Line breaks"
First line with two trailing spaces.  
Second line.
@end demo

@callout .warn
Don't indent paragraphs with tabs or spaces — this can cause unexpected formatting.
@end callout
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Emphasis
@divider

| syntax | output |
| --- | --- |
| `**text**` or `__text__` | **bold** |
| `*text*` or `_text_` | *italic* |
| `***text***` | ***bold and italic*** |

@demo
- `**bold**` → **bold**
- `*italic*` → *italic*
- `***bold and italic***` → ***bold and italic***
- `Love**is**bold` → Love**is**bold
@end demo

@callout .warn
For mid-word emphasis, use asterisks (`*`) not underscores — behavior with underscores varies between processors.
@end callout
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Blockquotes
@divider

| syntax | output |
| --- | --- |
| `> text` | blockquote |
| `>` on blank line | paragraph break within blockquote |
| `>> text` | nested blockquote |

@demo
> This is a blockquote.

> Multi-paragraph blockquote, first paragraph.
>
> Second paragraph.

> Outer level
>
>> Nested level
@end demo
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Lists
@divider

| syntax | output |
| --- | --- |
| `1.` prefix | ordered list |
| `-`, `*`, or `+` prefix | unordered list |
| indent by 2–4 spaces | nested list |

@demo "Ordered list"
1. First item
2. Second item
3. Third item
   1. Indented item
   2. Another indented item
4. Fourth item
@end demo

@demo "Unordered list"
- First item
- Second item
  - Nested item
  - Another nested item
- Third item
@end demo

@callout .warn
Use periods (`.`) not parentheses for ordered lists. Stick to one marker type (`-`, `*`, or `+`) per unordered list.
@end callout
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Code
@divider

| syntax | output |
| --- | --- |
| `` `code` `` | inline code |
| ` ``` ` fence | fenced code block |
| 4 spaces indent | indented code block |
| ` ``` lang ` | syntax highlighted block |

@demo "Inline code"
Use the `print()` function to output text.
@end demo

@demo "Code block"
```py
if __name__ == "__main__":
    print("Hello, World!")
```
@end demo
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Links
@divider

| syntax | output |
| --- | --- |
| `[label](url)` | inline link |
| `[label](url "title")` | link with tooltip |
| `[label][ref]` + `[ref]: url` | reference-style link |
| `<url>` | auto-linked URL |

@demo
[__Visit Google__](__https://www.google.com__)

[__Hover for a title__](__https://www.google.com__ "I'm a tooltip!")
@end demo
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Images
@divider

| syntax | output |
| --- | --- |
| `![alt](url)` | inline image |
| `![alt][ref]` | reference-style image |

@demo
![A placeholder image](__https://placehold.co/600x200__)
@end demo
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Horizontal Rules
@divider

| syntax | output |
| --- | --- |
| `---` | `<hr>` |
| `***` | `<hr>` |
| `___` | `<hr>` |

@demo
Above the rule.

---

Below the rule.
@end demo

@callout .warn
Put blank lines before and after horizontal rules to avoid them being interpreted as heading underlines.
@end callout
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Escaping
@divider

Prefix any special character with a backslash (`\`) to render it literally.

| characters you can escape |
| --- |
| `\` `` ` `` `*` `_` `{}` `[]` `()` `#` `+` `-` `.` `!` `\|` |

@demo
\* This is not italic \*

\# This is not a heading
@end demo
@end card

# Extended Syntax
@divider

@card .primary
## Tables
@divider

| syntax | description |
| --- | --- |
| `\|` pipes | column separators |
| `---` | header row separator |
| `:---` | left-align column |
| `:---:` | center-align column |
| `---:` | right-align column |

@demo "Basic table"
| Name | Role | Status |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Alice | Engineer | Active |
| Bob | Designer | Active |
| Carol | Manager | Away |
@end demo

@demo "Aligned columns"
| Left | Center | Right |
| :--- | :---: | ---: |
| apples | bananas | cherries |
| one | two | three |
@end demo

@callout .info
Tables support inline formatting: bold, italic, inline code, and links. Headings, block elements, and images inside cells are not supported.
@end callout
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Syntax Highlighting
@divider

Add a language identifier after the opening fence to enable syntax highlighting.

| common identifiers |
| --- |
| `js` `ts` `py` `html` `css` `json` `md` `bash` `sql` `yaml` |

@demo
```js
function greet(name) {
  return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}
```
@end demo

@demo
```json
{
  "name": "Marque",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "A Markdown-based site builder"
}
```
@end demo
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Strikethrough
@divider

| syntax | output |
| --- | --- |
| `~~text~~` | ~~strikethrough~~ |

@demo
~~The world is flat.~~ We now know that the world is round.
@end demo
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Task Lists
@divider

| syntax | output |
| --- | --- |
| `- [ ] task` | unchecked checkbox |
| `- [x] task` | checked checkbox |

@demo
- [x] Write the docs
- [x] Add syntax highlighting
- [ ] Add dark mode
- [ ] Publish v1.0
@end demo
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Footnotes
@divider

| syntax | description |
| --- | --- |
| `[^1]` | inline footnote reference |
| `[^1]: text` | footnote definition (anywhere in doc) |
| `[^label]` | word-based identifier |

@demo
Here's a sentence with a footnote.[^1]

And one with a named reference.[^note]

[^1]: This is the first footnote.
[^note]: Named footnotes work too.
@end demo
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Heading IDs
@divider

| syntax | description |
| --- | --- |
| `## Title {#custom-id}` | custom anchor ID on a heading |
| `[link](#custom-id)` | link to that anchor |

@demo
### My Section {#my-section}

[Jump to My Section](#my-section)
@end demo
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Highlight
@divider

| syntax | output |
| --- | --- |
| `==text==` | highlighted text |

@demo
I need to highlight these ==very important words==.
@end demo
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Subscript and Superscript
@divider

| syntax | output | example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `~text~` | subscript | H~2~O |
| `^text^` | superscript | X^2^ |

@demo
H~2~O is the chemical formula for water.

$E = mc^2$ is Einstein's most famous equation.
@end demo
@end card

----
@card .primary
## Automatic URL Linking
@divider

Most Markdown processors will auto-link bare URLs. Wrap in backticks to prevent linking.

@demo
https://www.marque.dev

`https://www.marque.dev` — not linked
@end demo
@end card

# Best Practices
@divider

@card
- Leave blank lines before and after block elements (headings, lists, blockquotes, code blocks)
- Don't indent paragraphs with spaces or tabs
- Use `*` for emphasis rather than `_` for mid-word compatibility
- Use `-` consistently as your unordered list marker
- Use periods (`.`) not parentheses for ordered lists
- Always add a space after `#` in headings
- Prefer fenced code blocks (` ``` `) over indented ones
@end card
